vectorData.altText: 7. Which class of epithelium is one cell layer thick and has surface cells that are just as tall as wide in shape?
That's right!  Simple cuboidal epithelium contain a single layer of cells that are as tall as wide in shape.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

Ask yourself two questions:
Does every cell touch the basement membrane? 
Yes? then it’s “simple”: 1 cell thick
found at sites of molecular transfer 
No? then it’s “stratified”: >1 cell thick
found at sites needing protection
What is the shape of the cells at the exposed surface? 
if flat, then it’s “squamous”
if height  width, then it’s “cuboidal”
if height > width, then it’s “columnar”
Any specializations of note?
microvilli?
cilia?
goblet cells?
include this information in the description
